  "prompt": "Can Indians work for NASA?",
  "response": "Yes, Indians can work for NASA. While NASA primarily hires U.S. citizens, they also consider applicants from other countries for certain positions, particularly those with specialized skills or expertise that may not be readily available in the U.S. Additionally, many individuals of Indian origin work at NASA or have collaborated with NASA through various projects, partnerships, or as contractors. \n\nTo work at NASA as a non-U.S. citizen, individuals may need to explore roles that allow for foreign workers, such as through internships, research collaborations, or at private companies that have contracts with NASA. Having advanced degrees in relevant fields such as engineering, computer science, or the sciences can enhance opportunities for working with NASA or in related industries.",
